cruellest, most barbaric and uncivilised</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
IMHO, there's one important thing everyone who discusses the possibility of a seige on Baghdad is overlooking.<br>
<br>
This would not be a 'seige' in the traditional sense, as related to a fortress or walled town.  There is nothing to physically stop civilians from walking/driving out of the city or defecting military from coming out to surrender.<br>
<br>
I imagine there will be the expected disruption of food/water/etc to the capitol city..but I would also imagine that there will be a large amount of food and water stores with the surrounding forces in order to accomodate anyone peacefully departing the city.<br>
<br>
The only people who won't leave..who wouldn't be allowed to leave without fully surrendering..are the ones being targeted by the seige.<br>
<br>
The only way the Saddam regieme could prevent civilians and deserters from leaving would be to shoot them before they managed to get out.  While it might be argued that shooting a deserter in wartime is at least somewhat understandable, I would hope that there would be an immediate Internatiional outcry if fleeing citizenry were to be gunned down by Republican Guardsmen. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.whitetoweronline.com"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.whitetoweronline.com/hall/icons/barth-sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=timberwind@nuclearspace>timberwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/30/03 7:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=405.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Were not winning!</span><hr size=1> Talche,<br>
