However So far as Iran is concerned you may wish to consider the following points. (Copied from an e-mail sent to me by somebody I have been corresponding with on this, this was part of the response to a copy of my last post, which I e-mailed to him for comment, It includes some important additional information)<br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>1)The Iranian air force is intact and very well equipped.  In addition to the numerous Phantom F5's inherited from the Shah (out of date but we were using them until recently) they have the former Iraqi air force which Saddam gave them before the last Gulf war.  This includes at least 30 Mig 29's, the *most up to date* Russian air-superiority fighter which, as I understand it, is superior in technical terms to *any* US fighter.<br>
 <br>
2) The Iranian air defence system is intact and will be very extensive.  I do not know for sure but I expect that they have up to date Russian or Chinese SAM's in large numbers as well probably as US Stingers from Arghanistan.  If the USAF attacks Iran it will suffer serious damage.  We are talking maybe 2-3 months to secure air superiority using *all* of the Fighter-Bomber type aircraft that are currently engaged in Iraq.  That would still leave the B52's for bombing but they are more suited to carpet bombing that precision stuff.  <br>
 <br>
3) It is reported in the Times yesterday that the US is almost out of stock of cruise missiles and precision munitions.  I understand this to mean *total* stocks and not merely those deployed to the Gulf.  No doubt the military-industrial complex will be working overtime but shock and awe will soon become impossible because there simply aren't enough missiles and bombs available for it.  If they don't have this kind of stuff it will be *much* more difficult to degrade the Iranian air defence network and other military infrastructure.<br>
 <br>
4) Iran also has submarines and anti-ship missiles I believe.<br>
 <br>
5) In view of the above if I was the Iranian leader and I decided to go for it I would:  (i) wait until the Americans were indulged in one of their mass air attacks on Bagdhad (so most of their FB's were up North in Iraq);  (ii) launch a Pearl Harbour style surprise attack against the US Navy Carriers in the Gulf and airbases in Kuwait using &quot;maximum force&quot; - ie my entire air force to sink the carriers and missiles at the bases.  I would simultaneously attack the carriers with my submarines and anti-ship missiiles.<br>
<br>
I believe that my strategy would achieve complete success.  I would sink all of the Carriers and devastate the Air Bases.  Some of the returning US planes might not even be able to land in Kuwait.  The Americans are not expecting such an attack and their formidable air defences (Patriots in Kuwait and Destroyers etc. with SAM's) are no doubt deployed against incoming Iraqi Scuds from the North.  I would probably then have air superiority over the coalition or at least broad equality and military victory for the &quot;axis of evil&quot; would be inevitable unless, of course, the Americans resorted to nuclear weapons.  <br>
<br>
Since they probably would do so (the humiliation would be so great). I would want to conduct a public nuclear test first.<br>
 <br>
)-:<br>
 <br>
The same comments largely apply to N.Korea and Syria, mututis mutandis (legal expression:  change details as necessary).  N.Korea probably has nukes already and it certainly has the ability to make them.  I would guess that the production lines are working overtime in preparation for an invasion of the South once the main combat strength of the US Army is tied down in Iraq.  As you know they have a reprocessing plant.  How much plutonium a month do you think they will be able to produce?  All I know is that we sold 50,000 Kg's of plutonium to the US in the 1980's because they did not have enough for the Reagan arms build up.  I believe that this was only about 10% of the UK stocks of plutonium at the time.  As I understand it, it would be enough to make about  3000-5000 A-Bombs of the Fat Man (Nagasaki) type - 10 - 15 Kg's per bomb.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
